▶ {tlhIngan nISwI' beH:sen:nolink}
   {nISwI' HIch motlh HoS Hal qengwI' naQ tIq je lurarlu'bogh 'oH tlhIngan nISwI' beH'e'. SuvwI' vI' Dub naQvam 'ej ray' HopDaq bachlu'meH chuqna' ghurmoH naQvam.:sen:nolink}
  "Klingon Disruptor Rifle
   The Klingon disruptor rifle is a standard hand held disruptor, attached to an extended power supply stock. This serves to steady the aim of a warrior and increase the effective range for distance targeting."[2]

This exclamation is not the equivalent of "hello". The greeted party is expected to simply begin speaking rather than return the greeting.[2; 3]

Note that this exclamation is in clipped Klingon. The grammatical way to ask "What do you want?" would be {nuq DaneH?:sen:nolink}[2]

